    "Each self-attention head m at layer l consists of the key (K), query(Q) and value (V) linear layers.",
    "Unlike in the FFT fine-tuning method, only the bias terms b l are considered during fine-tuning:",
    "Multiple attention heads are then combined using an attention mechanism and fed into the MLP with layer-norm (LN).",
    "The biases from the query, key and value layers, attention and normalisation layers are the only fine-tuned parameters of the network.",
